@node "config" "Config GUI"


 Once you have all programs installed...

 In AmIRC type /rx Ctcpgui.rexx and the GUI should open....

 GUI should open... if all is installed correctly.....

 IF Gui does not open.. try to open it again.. if it say you already 
 have it open.... click quit..

 Ok.. try a smaller .info file before you try to open GUI again..

 
 First page of GUI::

 Info-- basic info.....

 Page #2

   Fileversion ---  Turn FILEVER On/Off, On- lets people request verison of install files.
   Multiversion -- read the ctcp command filever in what is CTCP
   File version -- read the ctcp command filever in what is CTCP
   Rate-Exchange-- Lets people request currency rates via CTCP command.
   Commodities --- Turn Commodities requests On/Off

 Page #3

 Snapshot page... 
  
 This page has to option for Snapshot.

 Turn it off/on..  Pick program.  Delete the snapshots for Ram:T/ after 
 sending.  Gif on/off

 SnapSafe On/Off.  Play Wav when Snapshot is finished. Time Out for SnapSafe.

 Turn Gif off is your workbench has more than 8 planes since Tapgif will
 not convert it to gif...

 Cybergrab is for cybergfx or users with a 020 and above.....
   
 Program path also need to include the file names....

 Page #4

 User Config... some extras you have.. use MUI bubble info for more help.

 Auto Data & Boards are auto config via identify librarys... if it reads 
 something wrong in you system eamil the identify author, read identify 
 docs.....

 Page #5

 Personal DAta

 Pretty simple stuff.... the birthday and year click on it, its a slider.

 Web Info

 Pretty simple again.... just fill in the blanks...


 Then click save & quit.....

@endnode 

@node "ctcp" "What is Custom_CTCP"

  @{b}Custom_CTCP.amirx@{ub} is a arexx script AmIRC looks for any time it recieves a 
  Unknown CTCP command. The Script is started automatically.

  Custom_CTCP.amirx started out to as a small script just to stop Unkown CTCP 
  commands but from user input it has grown in to a Extension of AmIRC...

  Added CTCP Commands:
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Commodities    " link "commd"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Stats          " link "stats"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Filever        " link "filever"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Lamer_Alert    " link "lamer_alert"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Picture        " link "picture"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Face           " link "picture"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Waffle         " link "Waffle"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> SnapShot       " link "Snapshot"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> SnapShot Gif   " link "Snapgif"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> CHelp          " link "chelp"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> CHelp <Command>" link "chelp"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Setup          " link "setup"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> CVersion       " link "cversion"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> HomePage       " link "homepage"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> URL            " link "homepage"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Email          " link "email"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Needs          " link "needs"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Where          " link "where"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> FuckOff        " link "fuckoff"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Lamer          " link "lamer"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> ShutUP         " link "shutup"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Bye            " link "bye"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Hello          " link "hello"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Pizza          " link "pizza"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Rate           " link "rate"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Convert        " link "convert"}
@{" /CTCP <nick|Channel> Compic         " link "compic"}
@endnode
@node "stats"
 
 @{b} /CTCP <nick|Channel> Stats   @{ub}

  -JohnDoe- DOB: 07  Febuary  1961  Married SEX: male
   Height:
   Weight:
   Occupation:
   Hobbies:

  this is a return of a STATS command.. all the above info needs to be configured 
  in the GUI, and it also has the option to turn it off...
@endnode



@node "FileVer"
  @{b} /CTCP <nick|channel> FILEver <file> @{ub}     

  This is used to get the versions of certain files on other users computer..

  i.e.  /ctcp johndoe Filever iff.library  

  -Bossman^- File: System:Libs/iff.library 
             Version: 23.2 
             Date: 24.05.93 
             Misc: (-: by Christian A. Weber :-)

   
   filename can be any file ending with one of this extensions....

     .library  
     .device
     .class
     .codec
     .datatypes
     .gadget
     .images
     .mcc
     .mcp
     .mui

  I also made a script two script to use with Filever:

  @{b} Mulverreq.amrix  @{ub}  

  You can make a button in AmIRC with this command  /rx mulverreq.amirx %a
  you can select any number of users with the multiple select option in AmIRC
  a file requestor should open, and you can select file(s) shift click for more
  than one file....click OK

  a ctcp request will be sent to each user.....


  Configuring Mulverreq.amirx

  Mulverreq.amirx  needs two config options:

  Show Local:  Do you want Filver to version the file on your system.

  How Show: IF show local how do you want your version shown, either in a 
            requestor, or echoed to AmIRC..

  All is configured in the GUI..


@{b} Filever.amrix  @{ub}  

  syntax:  /rx filever <nick> <file> 
  
  the above command will send a /ctcp <nick> filever <file> to channel
  then will version the same file on you system and output the results..

  If you have show local turned off,, just use /ctcp <nick> filever <file>

  
  Configuring Filever.amirx

  Filever.amirx  needs two config options:

  Show Local:  Do you want Filver to version the file on your system.

  How Show: IF show local how do you want your version shown, either in a 
            requestor, or echoed to AmIRC..

  All is configured in the GUI..
@endnode
