@node "Rate"

@{b} /CTCP <nick> Rate <amount> <currency1> TO <currency2> <Y>  @{ub}

Rate exchange

This is a Currency Convertor.. 

Major update for v6.5, the data is converted via web pages in real time.

Only added the Y add the end if you wish channel output.....

amount = 1 to 10000000000 

currency1 & currency2 three digit coded for the currency.. look at the 
the exchange-rate file for all supported currencies....

example /ctcp Bossman^ 100 usd to GBp

you get this as a private notice , add a Y on the end output goes to 
the channel.

-Bossman^-  100 AMERICAN DOLLARS  will get You  62.95 BRITISH POUNDS

@endnode

@node "Convert"

@{b} /CTCP <nick|channel> Convert <amount> <type> <Y>      @{ub}

Convert: Converts the following....

     miles (mil) to kilometers (km)
     kilometers (km) to miles (mil)
     inches (in) to centimeters (cm)
     centimeters (cm) to inches (in)
     feet (ft) to meters (m)
     meters (m) to feet (ft)
     ounce (oz) to grams (g)
     grams(g) to ounces (oz)
     pounds (lbs) to kilograms (kg)
     kilograms (kg) to pounds(lbs)
     Fahrenheit(°F) to Celsius(°C)
     Celsius(°C) to Fahrenheit(°F)
     
example:

 /ctcp Bossman^ convert 10 ft Y {Y for channel output}')

output:

 <Bossman^> 10 Feet  is equal to  3.04 Metre(s)

@endnode


@node "Reqs" "Requirements"

 @{b}HARDWARE REQUIREMENTS@{ub}

 - Amiga Computer with Hard drive

 @{b}NEEDED SOFTWARE@{ub}

 - AmIRC 
 - AmiTCP compatible stack (AmiTCP, Miami or TermiteTCP)
 - MUIrexx 3.0a          (on Aminet)
 - rexxreqtools.library
 - rexxsupport.library
 - rexxkuang11.library   (included)
 - rexxtricks.library    (from aminet)
 - rexxidentify.library  (from aminet)
 - identify.library      (from aminet)
 - CRSnap.lzx            (from aminet)
 - CyberGrab.lha         (from aminet)
 - tapgif12.lha          (from aminet)
 - VersionWB.lha         (from aminet)
 - MUIRequest.lha        (from aminet)

@endnode

