@node "install" "Installation"

  @{b}MANUAL INSTALLATION Custom_CTCP package@{ub}

  

Files Included:

Custom_CTCP.guide             where every you want/

    All need to be installed in AmIRC/rexx/

ctcpdoubler.amirx         --- Version Reply
CTCPGUI.rexx              --- Config GUI
CTCPGUIcmd.rexx           --- Commands for GUI
custom_ctcp.amirx         --- CTCP Command script
MulVerReq.amirx           --- Multiple Filever Request script
Filever.amirx             --- Single Filever with local echo


Files in AmIRC/rexx/Custom_ctcp/

    One of the below files needs to be renamed to suit your system.
    for interlaced systems, Custom_ctcp300-I-.info seems to be the best
    for non-interlaced screens 300 or 400 NI seems to be the best.
    Rename the file to Custom_CTCP.info. 

    

Custom_CTCP200-I-.info         ----RWED
Custom_CTCP250-I-.info         ----RWED
Custom_CTCP250-NI-.info        ----RWED
Custom_CTCP300-I-.info         ----RWED
Custom_CTCP300-NI-.info        ----RWED
Custom_CTCP350-NI-.info        ----RWED
Custom_CTCP400-NI-.info        ----RWED

*** note ***

CTCPdata -- is created by the Gui and saved here.....if your upgrading 
            move you CTCPdata to Amirc/rexx/custom_ctcp/ before opening
            the GUI....





The below programs need to be installed unless you already have...
best place to install is in C: but only VersionWB has to be in C:
other or configurable.

In the indentifyv7.lha you need the two libs installed in LIBs:

CyberGrab12.lha                (Read the docs for more info)
Identifyv7.lha                 (Read the docs for more info)
tapgif12.lha                   (Read the docs for more info)
VersionWB.lha                  (Read the docs for more info)
CRSnap.lzx                     (Read the docs for more info)


You also need MUIRexx version 3.0a installed in Sys:rexxc/ under the name of
Muirexx

@endnode



